TY  - JOUR
T1  - That Word “Organization”
AU  - Urwick, L.F.
Y1  - 1976/01/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1976.4408773
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1976.4408773
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 89
EP  - 92
VL  - 1
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the importance and various meanings of the word organization within the field of management science. For management education students, the author finds that the word is used in an aloof manner, most frequently in the United States. He attributes this occurrence to the different ways in which the word is used, including the way in which a company is managed and also as another word for the company itself. Other definitions also exist and the author argues that having so many meanings for one word dilutes its importance within the professional world.
AB  - The article discusses the importance and various meanings of the word organization within the field of management science. For management education students, the author finds that the word is used in an aloof manner, most frequently in the United States. He attributes this occurrence to the different ways in which the word is used, including the way in which a company is managed and also as another word for the company itself. Other definitions also exist and the author argues that having so many meanings for one word dilutes its importance within the professional world.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1976.4408773
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1976.4408773
Y2  - 2026/04/24
